sql:
SELECT enrichment_ratio
FROM cluster_terms
WHERE cluster_id = 0 AND q_val < 0.05;

external_knowledge:
- Enrichment ratio refers to the ratio of term size to background size; 
- Top clusters are clusters with the highest average enrichment ratios; 
- Top terms are terms with the highest enrichment ratios within top clusters.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(cluster_id) AS cluster_count
FROM project_clusters
WHERE project_id = 0;

SELECT cluster_name, creation_date
FROM clusters
ORDER BY creation_date DESC;

SELECT COUNT(term_id) AS term_count
FROM project_terms
WHERE project_id = 1;
